Class GracefullShutdownParticle

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MetaParticle, Particle

    public class GracefullShutdownParticle
extends AbstractMetaParticle
implements MetaParticle
    The gracefullShutdownParticle is a meta particle indicating that the topology must prepare itself for a shutdown. After this particle no other meta or data particles will be sent.

        public boolean equalMetaParticle(MetaParticle other)
        Description copied from interface: MetaParticle
        Check if this MetaParticle is equal to another Particle. MetaParticles need to implement their own equals method, which ignores the originId. This method is used by the SyncBuffer in order to remove duplicate MetaParticles.
        Specified by:
        equalMetaParticle in interface MetaParticle
        Overrides:
        equalMetaParticle in class AbstractMetaParticle
        Parameters:
        other - Other MetaParticle used for comparison
        Returns:
        True if this object is equal to another instance of a MetaParticle, with the exception of the originId.
